WHAT: api/types/ and api/errors/ files must not import from api/traits/ — VOs and DTOs are pure data; importing a domain trait signals the type carries behavior and belongs in core/.
WHY: A type in api/types/ that imports api/traits/ has embedded behavior coupling; it cannot be used as a plain value type in test utilities or serialization layers without pulling in the full trait ecosystem.
BEFORE (violation):
  // api/types/pipeline.rs
  use crate::api::traits::Processor; // types/ importing traits/ — forbidden
  pub struct Pipeline { processor: Box<dyn Processor> }
AFTER (compliant):
  // Option A — type holds behavior: move to core/types/
  // core/types/pipeline.rs
  use crate::api::traits::Processor;
  pub(crate) struct Pipeline { processor: Box<dyn Processor> }
  // Option B — keep as VO: use a generic type parameter constrained at the call site
  pub struct Pipeline<P> { processor: P } // no trait import in the file
  // call site: Pipeline::<DefaultProcessor>::new(DefaultProcessor::new())
EDGE CASES:
  - Box<dyn Trait> as a struct field: this requires the trait import; Option A (move to core/) is the correct fix
  - api/errors/ files: same rule — error types must be plain data structs, not trait importers

